The wind South and the Thermometer 76 degrees work all day for John D.Harrington on his cook house. Shinglell the roof &c.

The wind South West Thermometer 80Â° in the shade work 114 day for Mr John D. Harrington on his cookrun laying floo Took my boat in the afternoon and went to Bar Harbor to stop all night to take the Str for S.W. Harbor heavy thunder & lightning with rain in evening

The wind South West Thermometer 80Â° in the shade work 114 day for Mr John D. Harrington on his cookrun laying floo Took my boat in the afternoon and went to Bar Harbor to stop all night to take the Str for S.W. Harbor heavy thunder & lightning with rain in evening

The wind South West Thermometer 90 at Bar Harbor Took the New Steamer Mt Desert and went to South West Harbor & come back on the Lewiston to distribute some of my Hotel Cards among the passengers. Took the Str Sea Flower at Bar Harbor and came home at night

The wind South West Thermometer 90 at Bar Harbor Took the New Steamer Mt Desert and went to South West Harbor & come back on the Lewiston to distribute some of my Hotel Cards among the passengers. Took the Str Sea Flower at Bar Harbor and came home at night

The wind South West Thermometer 90 at Bar Harbor Took the New Steamer Mt Desert and went to South West Harbor & come back on the Lewiston to distribute some of my Hotel Cards among the passengers. Took the Str Sea Flower at Bar Harbor and came home at night

The wind South West Thermometer 90 at Bar Harbor Took the New Steamer Mt Desert and went to South West Harbor & come back on the Lewiston to distribute some of my Hotel Cards among the passengers. Took the Str Sea Flower at Bar Harbor and came home at night
The wind West North West Thermometer 74 degrees Hoed my beans & Corn received letter from Mrs Henry Chapin and circulars from several advertising agents.
The wind Westerly in the forenoon and South West in the afternoon Thermometer 60 degrees work in my garden and unowed around the house.
The wind North East in morning Thermometer 68 degrees Work all day for J. D. Harrington on his cook room The wind Southerly in the afternoon

The wind Southerly Thermometer 70 degrees went to a Religious meeting in the forenoon by R C Richard Mitchel And in the afternoon by Mr. Pierson of Boston Mr Piersons meeting was held at Dr E.J.  Frenchs tent by C.J.Guptills house.

The wind Southerly and overcast Thermometer 50 Went to South Gouldsboro Steam boat wharf to cary Miss Greenleaf to take the Str Mt Deserrt. Mowed some hay in the afternoon and poled some in the barn at night.

The wind Southerly and overcast Thermometer 50 Went to South Gouldsboro Steam boat wharf to cary Miss Greenleaf to take the Str Mt Deserrt. Mowed some hay in the afternoon and poled some in the barn at night.

The wind Southerly and overcast Thermometer 50 Went to South Gouldsboro Steam boat wharf to cary Miss Greenleaf to take the Str Mt Deserrt. Mowed some hay in the afternoon and poled some in the barn at night.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 70 degrees mowed in the forenoon and in ther afternoon went to Bar Harbor to telegraph to Wm Cole at New York Stoped at Bar Harbor all night waiting for a dept
The wind Southerly Thermometer 70 degrees mowed in the forenoon and in ther afternoon went to Bar Harbor to telegraph to Wm Cole at New York Stoped at Bar Harbor all night waiting for a dept
The wind South and rainy and foggy all day at 10 Am no despalh and came home Thermometer 51 degrees received letters from M Gallent &Co. & marden & Rowell.
The wind South and rainy and foggy all day at 10 Am no despalh and came home Thermometer 51 degrees received letters from M Gallent &Co. & marden & Rowell.
The wind North pleasant Thermometer 59 degrees took care of hay that was mowed before the storm. The wind South West at 4.P.M.
The wind North West in the forenoon & South West in the afternoon Thermometer 62Â° work all day haying wrote letters to Mrs Bessie E Crant and M. Gallart &Co. received letter from Miss Guenlief
The wind Easterly Thermometer 60 and overcast mowed in the forenoon but did not open or spread my for hay day
The wind Southerly Thermometer 69 degrees Went to West Gouldsboro with mail

A party of 9 from Bar Harbor to Eureka House to dinner. The wind Southerly Thermometer 69 Went to West Gouldsboro with ail Route 365Had a party of 9 at the Eureka House to dinner in addition to the other boarders. received Check for carrying mail from Post Office Department Route 365
The wind North North West and very pleasant. Thermometer 72 degrees went to Bar Harbor after some groceries for the house hired the mail carried on route 365
The wind South East Thermometer 59 degrees Went to Ellsworth. to take advantage of the Insobuert act Employed A P Wiswell Came back at night moderate rain
The wind Easterly Thermometer 58 degrees heavy rain all day Went to West Gouldsboro with the mail.
The wind North West Thermometer 67 degrees Finished the mast step in the Hayward yatch. Went to South Gouldsboro wharf with my boarders trunks
The wind very moderate Thermometer Settled up with my boarders and I carried them to South Gouldsboro Steam boat wharf.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 60Â° and thick with fog Went to West Gouldsboro with the Mail. received letter from A.P. Wiswell Esq
The wind Westerly in the morning Thermometer 70 Went to Ellsworth Came home in the afternoon arrived at 10 P.M.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 65 degrees Went to West Gouldsboro with mail received letter from Chas J Guptill of Steuben Sold my interest in a boat to Mr Ira Foss received $10
The wind Easterly and Thermometer 68 degrees Went to South Gouldsboro wharf to Carry Miss Fannie Tracy to Boat In afternoon worked in the old house fixing it up to move in
Calm and drizzling rain all day Thermometer 62Â° Went to West Gouldsboro with the mail
The wind S.S.E. Thermometer 58 degrees and rainy all day. Went to West Gouldsboro with the Mail then to the Town House to the State Election back to W. Gouldsboro took the mail and came home.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 52Â° Went to West Gouldsbo with the Mail. Wrote letter to Mr Helen Stevens
The wind South West. Thermometer 62 degrees had a summons left to appear to the Court held at Ellsworth. from M. Gallent &Co. Went to Birch Harbor to carry Jennie Tracy. work all day on old house.
The wind Easterly and overcast. Thermometer 49 degrees Went to West Gouldsboro with the Mail.
Calm in morning very heavy frost Thermometer 26 Went to West Gouldsboro with the Mail
The wind South West. Thermometer 45 degrees Went to Ellsworth to make out a list of Creditors I being Insolient. Came home in the evening
The wind Southerly Thermometer 45Â° Went to West Gouldsboro with the mail. received letter from Helen Stevens.
The wind South West Went to Cranberry Isles to see Emma Spurling Started for home at 5 oclock P.M. at dark the wind North West arrived home at 8 P.M. received notice

The wind South West Thermometer 67 degrees Went to West Gouldsboro received letter from RH Kittredge &Co and wrote letter to R H Kittredge & Co and to A P Wiswell Esq. oath o G W Tracy as Post master.
The wind Easterly and drizzling rain Thermometer 52 degrees Went to West Gouldsboro with the mail.
The wind very moderate Easterly Thermometer 54 and drizzling rain in the afternoon Went to South Gouldsboro to Carry E A Keating & family.
The wind North West And Thermometer 36 Went to West Gouldsboro with the Mail. heavy Snow Squalls in forenoon.
The wind South West Thermometer 60Â° Went to West Gouldsboro with the Mail Repaired the Schr AGBrooks wheel. received letter from Boston Traveler Office.
The wind West N. West. and a very fresh breeze Thermometer 33 degrees went to West Gouldsboro with the mail.
The wind Westerly Thermometer 44 degrees Went to South Gouldsboro to get Leonard Bunker to Cary the mail for me tomorrow.

The wind Easterly In the morning the Thermometer down to 20 and gradually went up to 40 degrees. Went down on the Southern part of Turtle Island and got 2 boat loads of wood. In the afternoon thick with snow.

The wind Easterly Thermometer 35 degrees Snow and rain to gather Went to West gouldsboro with the mail, good Sleighign at West Gouldsboro Hauled wood from the shore to the house at night Let David Weare have my horse to go on Mail Router.

The wind West South West Went down Turtle Island to work for Wm. Handy putting in Window frames in his house. getting it ready fo Wm Leavy to move in. Very fresh breeze and the Thermometer 40 degrees. came home at night.
Calm in the morning at 8. AM. the wind breezed up to the North. Went down on Turtle Island and worked all day for Wm Handy hanging doors and setting partitions &c.

The wind North West fresh breeze and the Thermometer 28 degrees Went to West Gouldsboro with the Mail on Route 191 Via Prospect. received check from Mr Wm. B. Viall for $12.38 for carrying mail one gr on Route 365. West Gouldsboro

The wind Southerly Thermometer 45 degrees Went to West Gouldsboro with the Mail. Capt L.B. Tracy burried at Winter Harbor in the afternoon. Who died on board his vessel at Kittery Point. at night rainy.

The wind Southerly Thermometer 45 degrees Went to West Gouldsboro with the Mail. Capt L.B. Tracy burried at Winter Harbor in the afternoon. Who died on board his vessel at Kittery Point. at night rainy.

The wind North East overcast Thermometer 32 degrees. Went to Ellsworth to the Second meeting of my Creditor at the Court of Insolvency accompanied by G. W. Tracy. Took my horse as far as Sullivan then got Asa Whites. Went to Ellsworth. and back to Sullivan with his Then took mine and came home in the Evening

The wind North East overcast Thermometer 32 degrees. Went to Ellsworth to the Second meeting of my Creditor at the Court of Insolvency accompanied by G. W. Tracy. Took my horse as far as Sullivan then got Asa Whites. Went to Ellsworth. and back to Sullivan with his Then took mine and came home in the Evening

The wind North East overcast Thermometer 32 degrees. Went to Ellsworth to the Second meeting of my Creditor at the Court of Insolvency accompanied by G. W. Tracy. Took my horse as far as Sullivan then got Asa Whites. Went to Ellsworth. and back to Sullivan with his Then took mine and came home in the Evening
The wind Westerly and Thermometer 41 degrees not any snow. or ice took some dishes out the Hotel Went to So. Gouldsboro and got. Leonard Bunker to carry the Mail.
The wind Northerly Thermometer 30 degrees Went to West Gouldsboro to see the Assignee not snow enough for Sleighing
The wind North East. and snowing all day Thermometer from 14 degrees up to 32 degrees. Went to Prospect Harbor and had sleigh shoes put on by E.W. Cleaves

The wind North wind moderate Thermometer at zero in the morning Went to So Gouldsboro according to the Summons. the defendents were arranged before judge Cleaves and settled it without coming to Trial wrote deed to Wm H Sargent in Evening.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 40 above moderate rain and snow all day. Went to West Gouldsboro. with the mail.
The wind North West pleasant Thermometer 32 degrees.

The wind from South West to W. Thermometer 40 degrees above 0 Went to West Gouldsboro with mail. received letter from the Auditor of the Treasury for the Post Office Department stahing check sent me No 14872 lost and payment stoped at Po in Portland
The wind North West. Thermometer 32Â° at noon Went to West Gouldsboro to carry shup pilts for J.F.K.
The wind Southerly and rainy all day fresh breeze in afternoon Thermometer 55 degrees Cut door throng from dining room to store room.
Wind North East. work 3/4 day shingling for Capt N.A.Bickford & finished work. and at night baited troll ready to go a fishing Thermometer 44 degrees
Wind South South West. Thermometer 67 catching mackerel for bait

The wind North West. Thermometer 12 above zero. Had the Horse Showed in forenoon. and in the afternoon went to Ellsworth via Trenton. to see Capt N. H. Higgins and pay the Insurance on house Stoped at the Lake house all night.
Calm all day and the Thermometer 40Â° Wrote letter to Mejsrs Sherman &Co. Marshall Mich. received the first copy of the Bangor Communicae
Calm in morning went out fishing and set troll in Egg Rock Channel got one 1 a half tubs of fish back in the afternoon wind South West fresh breeze Thermometer 57 degrees
The wind Southerly Thermometer 42Â° Went to Ellsworth with my horse after sheeting for bed

The wind North West. Thermometer 12 above zero. Had the Horse Showed in forenoon. and in the afternoon went to Ellsworth via Trenton. to see Capt N. H. Higgins and pay the Insurance on house Stoped at the Lake house all night.
The wind Southerly and overcast partially foggy went out fishing Thermometer 71 degrees,
The wind Southerly Thermometer 70 degrees work abt the house putting shelves in store room &e Recd card from G.L. Dennison
Calm all day and the Thermometer 42 degrees Wrote to Auditor of Treasury for a duplicate check No 14872
Wind Easterly and heavy rain in morning Cleared up in the afternoon made a floaling stage to dress fish on Thermometer 70Â°
The wind Southerly Thermometer 42Â° Went to Ellsworth with my horse after sheeting for bed

The wind moderate all day Westerly Thermometer down 4Â° degrees below zero in Ellsworth. Had stoughters made for a Harness and came home in the afternoon. Sold the Eureka House to Bessie E Grant of Camden and had the writings done by Wm Rand by attorney.
The wind Northerly in forenoon went out fishing Wind Southerly in afternoon Thermometer 72 Wrote letter to Geo M Waren Castine.
The wind Northerly in forenoon Went to Bar Harbor to Telegraph. The wind very moderate Southerly Started for home at 7p.m.
The wind North West. Thermometer 37 degrees received letter from Hugh Mckay Lotterie Agent at Canada.
Wind South West Thermometer. 60Â° Work about the fish house all day putting it in order to take care of fish.
The wind North West Thermometer 55Â° Got the goods and came home in afternoon

The wind North East. Thermometer 33 degrees above Work in the woods in the forenoon cutting firewood. In the evening witnessed the Solemnzing of the Marriage of Charles E Kingsley and Mijs Hannah Grover by Mr Palm

The wind moderate all day Westerly Thermometer down 4Â° degrees below zero in Ellsworth. Had stoughters made for a Harness and came home in the afternoon. Sold the Eureka House to Bessie E Grant of Camden and had the writings done by Wm Rand by attorney.
The wind North West in the morning Thermometer 32 and very pleasant. at night the wind out Southerly and indications of a Storm. Went to a Lyceum at Pacific Hall Winter Harbor

The wind very moderate all day and fine weather went out fishing from home in dora. Thermometer in the afternoon when I came in from fishing 80 degrees. received letter from Helen Stevens at Leadsvelle
The wind North West Thermometer 55Â° Got the goods and came home in afternoon
The wind Northerly in forenoon Went to Bar Harbor to Telegraph. The wind very moderate Southerly Started for home at 7p.m.

Wind North in forenoon fresh breeze went out to my troll wind blew so hard I could not pick it. In afternoon moderate went out to my troll and baited it at night very fresh Southerly Thermometer 49 degrees
Very moderate North East wind in forenoon Southerly in the afternoon Thermometer 75 degrees

The wind Southerly and clear. Thermometer 55Â° degree above. Caulked and painted boat Recd postal card from A.J. Chapman Esq Bangor. Filled out and acknowledged the Signing of an application for Pension for Nancy Joy.
The wind South South West Thermometer 28 above 0. Carried Capt AGerrish and wife up to his fathers in the forenoon and went after them in the afternoon.
The wind Northerly in forenoon Went to Bar Harbor to Telegraph. The wind very moderate Southerly Started for home at 7p.m.
The wind South South East and heavy rain all day Thermometer 40Â° above received Circular from Sherman &Co Marshall Michigan. A large body of snow matter
The wind Easterly in forenoon went out to my troll got two tubs of fish and came back about 4 oclock. wind Southerly and the Thermometer 37 degrees.
Thick with fog in morning at 10 Am cleared up Went out fishing very fresh breeze Southerly Thermometer 74 degrees

The wind Southerly and foggy Thermometer 51Â° at noon Went to prayer meeting Preaching in forenoon. And in the afternoon went to Baptism in this place. Hannah Newman, Augustus Newman, Alphena and Daniel Bickford, Mary Ann Giles, Emma Jane Myrick, and Joseph Bickford In the Evening went to meeting of the Lords supper by Wm Whicken
The wind North Easterly Thermometer 12 above Made shaft for Mr Nathan S. Bickford Pung in place of one I broke Thursday 13 going to East Sullivan Exhibition sent deeds to Ellsworth to be recorded
The wind Easterly Thermometer 68 degrees Wrote letter to Elias Hale & CC Vedall. Recd Letter from Elias J Hale
The wind Westerly and pleasant Thermometer 37 degrees above Went to West Gouldsboro with passengers. received notice from Narraguagus Lodge.
Wind Southerly and moderate all day. Went out fishing Thermometer 79 degrees Catching mackerel mornand night for troll bait
The wind Westerly. The Thermometer 56Â° above Puttied the boat and painted her Bought pig of F Toft 5 weeks old
The wind East North East and snowing all day Thermometer 14 degrees above zero. Mended horness apart of the day. wrote letter to Bessie E. Grant and C.C. Burrill
The wind South West and pleasant all day and the Thermometer 37 above. Went to a Religious Meeting in the evening
Wind Northerly in morning Went out fishing Wind Southerly in afternoon Thermometer 78 degrees received Check from the Post Office Department for &12.38 for Mail service on Route 365
The wind North East. Thermometer 54Â° Wrote letters to Mrs Proctor Smallidge, S.C. Forsaith, &Co, Thomas Bunker & E.A. Baker Recd Hotel Register from Mysrs Maynard &Co.
Wind Southerly heavy thunder and lightning in the morning and pleasant through the middle of the day. and very heavy thunder and lightning at night. Thermometer 59

The wind Southerly Thermometer 62 Went on a ride to the sands and to the Marsh accompanied by my wife and child Went to a religious meeting in the evening advertised in the Boston Daily Evening Traveler $1878 to be paid in year
The wind Southerly and wet and foggy Thermometer 51Â° work all day on boat putting in seals &e
The wind South East Thermometer 50 degrees went out to my troll fishing wrote letter to A. P. Wiswell
The wind North East. Thermometer. 12 above Went to West Gouldsboro to Carry James Bourgett to take the stage for Bucksport.
Calm in the morning went out fishing from home in dora. Wind South West in afternoon came home Thermometer 79 degrees
The wind very moderate Southerly Thermometer 42 and pleasant untill night when it began to rain.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 62 degrees helped J.F. Kingsley in the afternoon get his hay. Bought one half ton of hay and put it in T.R. Hammonds barn
The wind Southerly and foggy Thermometer 48 Wrote letters to Capt H.C. Guptill Calais work a little while on boat.
The wind South West Fresh breeze Thermometer 54 degrees. Went to Prospect Harbor after suit Oil Clothes and up to Stave Island after bait.
The wind North East. Thermometer. 12 above Went to West Gouldsboro to Carry James Bourgett to take the stage for Bucksport.
Moderate Southerly all day. Went out fishing from home in dora. back in afternoon Thermometer 75 degrees
Calm all day Thermometer 50 Administered the oath to the New P.M. Jennie Tracy in lieu of G.W. Tracy.
The wind South Easterly and foggy Thermometer 50 work about the house all day
The wind South West Fresh breeze Thermometer 54 degrees. Went to Prospect Harbor after suit Oil Clothes and up to Stave Island after bait.
The wind North East. Thermometer. 12 above Went to West Gouldsboro to Carry James Bourgett to take the stage for Bucksport.
The wind South East. and rainy in morning Thermometer 50 degrees. Wrote letters to S.C. Muney &Co. Worked on boat apart of the afternoon. Recd letter from S.C. Forsaith Red Speech from Han E Hale
The wind Northerly Thermometer 68Â° in the forenoon and overcast in the afternoon clear weather Thermometer 72Â° help J Kingsley all day haying.
Very fresh Southerly all day and rough Went out fishing from home in dora Thermometer 62 degrees
The wind North West Thermometer 20 above. hauled one load of wood on home lot.
The wind North East and snowing and blowing all day Thermometer 14 above Made sled shaft. for my self.
Wind North Thermometer 45 went to my troll in the morning found moorings parted and apart of the troll in a snarl. Took the troll up carrid it hom cleared it & baited and at night set it.
The wind South East foggy and rainy in morning Thermometer 50 degrees afternoon cleared up.
The wind North West. Thermometer 74 degrees Work for J.F. Kingsley haying. hauled in five loads
Wind North West all day and very fine weather Thermometer 78Â°
The wind South East. Thermometer 40 degrees above received duplicate check from the P.O. Department for the Quarter ending Sept 30. Wrote letter to G H Smith received letter from Hugh Mc Kay Canada.
The wind N.N. East snow and snow blowing all day. roads blocked the mail did not go Thermometer 13 above 0 Visited the School taught by Mr Phillips It being next to the last day of school.
Wind North East. Thermometer 44 went to the troll in the morning wind blew very fresh had to leave it & come in.
The wind North East and rainy Thermometer 57 hauled one load wood
The wind Southerly Thermometer 72 degrees work for J.F. Kingsley hauled in two loads of hay.
Wind North West all day Thermometer at Sun rush down to 50 degrees but warm in afternoon. went to my troll
The wind Westerly and Thermometer 37 degrees wrote letter to Wm B Viall of Bethel Vt. and Auditor of the Treasurer Washington
The wind North Thermometer 14 above zero. hauled one load of wood for Geo Gerrish.
The wind North East. Thermometer 38 degrees very fresh breeze. Went to Prospect Harbor after Hhd and hanging twine for nots
The wind North East and heavy rain all day. Thermomter 49Â° wrote letter to Mrs. Martin Pendleton at Lynn Recd letter from Geo Bagley work about the house. C.J. Guptill made each as school agt.
Wind North West in forenoon South West afternoon Went to my troll used salt bait bait very scarce mackerel has been plenty but have left Thermometer 71Â°.
The wind Southerly and Thermometer 32 degrees above zero. At Pm the wind came off N.West cold with snow squalls

The wind Westerly Thermometer 35 above 0 Went on Mark island and Married John K Norwood & Mifs Lillian S Wilkinson both of Gouldsboro. They were married at 3 Oclock in the afternoon. and I came home before the Sun set.
The wind North West in forenoon went out to my troll South West wind in afternoon Thermometer 59Â°
The wind Easterly and overcast. Thermometer 46Â°, fixed pen for pig and hauled wood from Esqr Rands meadow

The wind Westerly Thermometer 35 above 0 Went on Mark island and Married John K Norwood & Mifs Lillian S Wilkinson both of Gouldsboro. They were married at 3 Oclock in the afternoon. and I came home before the Sun set.
The wind North West Thermometer. 65 degrees
The wind Southerly Thermometer 58 moderate rain in the afternoon. Hauled one load of hay in barn in forenoon for J.F.K
The wind Southerly Thermometer 45 very moderate rain all the forenoon and in the afternoon went to Birch Harbor selling Sewing machine Casters.
The wind South Easterly and moderate. Went to my troll fishing from home. and using salt bait. got about 3/4 of a tub of fish Thermometer 68Â°
The wind North West Thermometer 6 degrees below zero
The wind South West and clear. Thermometer 54Â° Cut wood at the door wrote letter to G.W. Bagley

The wind Westerly Thermometer 35 above 0 Went on Mark island and Married John K Norwood & Mifs Lillian S Wilkinson both of Gouldsboro. They were married at 3 Oclock in the afternoon. and I came home before the Sun set.
Wind North in forenoon Went out to my troll wind Southerly in afternoon. Thermometer 60 and Showery tarred a herring net

The wind S.S. East in forenoon and very heavy rain In the afternoon cleared up Thermometer 70Â° degrees wrote letters to Geo S Peters and A White of Hingham work apart of the day on Express wagon for my self turning hub &e
Wind South very fresh breeze and Rough by a long hard pull got to my troll. bait from the Weir. Thermometer 60 degrees at 5 PM. received letter from Geo.M.Warren Esq
The wind Southerly Thermometer 45 degrees Set up leach barrel in the morning to make soap and then started out went to my horse to sell Sewing Machine Casters.
The wind Eastt fresh breeze and big snow storm Thermometer 10 above zero. Went in the woods cutting firewood stormed so hard came out at noon received letter from Helen Stevens
The wind Southerly Thermometer 50Â° hauled stone all day grading in front of house.
The wind Westerly Thermometer 20 above wrote letters to Portland Transcript Ellsworth Arrived Town Clerk. Mary Stanley E.S.Stevens of Ellsworth Hauled two loads of wood from upper damn.
Wind Westerly Thermometer 65 Registered letter to A.P.Wiswell with $15. enclosed the ballance due on my Insolvency Staid in from fishing to put Cork rope and sinker line on net.
The wind North West Thermometer 72 degrees Help J.F. Kingsley haul in 4 loads of hay. had party from Bar Harbor to stay over night
Wind South Easterly Thick with fog and rain did not go to my troll Thermometer 52 degrees.
Calm and thick with fog. Went out fishing heavy rain at noon Thermometer 57 degrees.
Wind Southerly all day Caught some mackerel at night for bait. Thermometer at 8 AM. 84 degrees.
Wind South West Went out fishing to the South of Egg rock using mackerel for bait from home in dora Thermometer. 71 degrees
Wind Southerly Went out fishing Thermometer 79 degrees.
Wind North all day very fresh breeze. blew so hard I could not go fishing staid home and Coopered Hhds &c Thermometer 71 degrees
Wind North West in forenoon Went ou fishing Wind South West in afternoon Wrote deed for P L Tracy in evening. Thermometer 60 degrees
Wind Southerly and moderate went out fishing from home in dora. Thermometer 70 degrees.
The wind South with a very fresh breeze and rough. Went out to my troll Thermometer at 4 P.M. 68 degrees.
The wind Northerly and pleasant with the Thermometer 80 degrees
Wind North North West Went out a fishing from home living on the Wm Handy place purchased by my wife May 28th Thermometer 61 degrees
Wind South West Went out fishing using herring for bait. fish not very plenty, a good school of haddock in the spring but hake are very scarce.
Wind South West Staid in from fishing to do other work went to Prospect Harbor to Cary My wife to make an Endorsment . on note
The wind South West and rough Went to my troll hake very scarce Thermometer in afternoon when I got home 70Â°
The wind Southerly and a very fresh breeze did not go a fishing Thermometer 70 degrees
The wind Southerly and thick with fog. did not go out to my troll Wrote letter to A.P. Eiswell Esq and John Bruinmer Thermometer 61 degrees
The wind Southerly Thermometer 82 degrees

Wind Southerly and Thermometer 70 degrees Wrote letter to Wm Handy Owner of Schr Old Chad Geo. M. Warren and to the Post Office Department last named letter for David Weare. Went out fishing afternoon
Wind Northerly in the forenoon. Went to my troll Wind Southerly in the afternoon. Thermometer 80. degrees
Wind North in the morning and hauled around to the Eastward. Went out to my troll overcast weather. and at night when I got home from my troll. the Thermometer 59 degrees.
The wind North East and blowing very fresh all day. could not pick my troll get a plenty of herring for bait. Thermometer. 69 degrees

Wind North East went to my net at the Southern point of Mark Island got 1/2 Bbl of herring wind bley very fresh could not get to my troll. Went ashore to the Silver Mine at Schoodic in the afternoon heavy rains
The wind North West very fresh breeze in forenoon but went down in afternoon. Thermometer 72 degrees at 3 P.M.
Wind Southerly Thermometer 80 degrees
Wind Southerly thick with fog. Thermometer 60 degrees. Went to State Election at the Town house in Gouldsboro.
The wind moderate Southerly and moderate rain all day. Thermometer 57 degrees. Work most all day at home on troll.
The wind Easterly and a very fresh breeze and tremendious rain all day at night wind went down Thermometer 55 degrees
The wind Southerly. Thermometer at 6 AM 54Â° Commenced making a wheel Schr Ella.
The wind South. rough weather for fishing Thermometer 49 degrees
The wind North West in forenoon and Calm in afternoon Went outfishing Thermometer 60 degrees.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 71 degrees
Wind Southerly Thermometer 50 degrees very fresh breeze and overcast. Work all day on wheel for Capt Sherman Spurling for the Schr Ella heavy shower at night
Wind North West and a very fresh breeze to much wind to go fishing Thermometer 55 degrees
Wind North West and very fresh breeze Went out fishing in dora from home making the fishing business my general employment. Thermometer 45 degrees.
Wind North West in the morning got 2 bushels of herring for bait in my net. Went out fishing Wind South South West in afternoon. and the Thermometer 31Â° in morning very heavy frost
Wind Southerly and thermometer 75 degrees did not go a fishing for the want of bait washed out fish for my self received letter from R H Bickford wrote one to Clarance Hane & Geo Warren.
Moderate Southerly wind all day day thick with fog in the forenoon and clear in the afternoon
Wind Southerly and thick with fog and drizzling rain all day Got new shoes on horse Thermometer 52Â°
Wind South Easterly and rain all day turned table legs for Reuben Rand Thermometer 50 degrees
Wind Southerly and clear Thermometer 74 got no bait in nets and. did not go a fishing Work most all day on wagon wheel for my self. A man hired to dig potatoes.
The wind West South West and thick with fog. Went out and set my troll at 10 Am Wind blowing a gale fog cleared came in an left my troll setting Thermometer 59Â°
Wind West North West fresh breeze in forenoon Made out quarterly returns for P.M. at Birch Harbor work apart of the day digging potatoes at 3 P.M Thermometer 62Â°
Wind Southerly and heavy frost Thermometer 34 in morning Went out fishing got a little. more than one tub of fish. Heavy frost at night.
Wind Southerly and pleasant all day Thermometer 72 degrees at noon.
The wind South South West blowing heavy and big sea running could not get out fishing and worked about home. Thermometer 47 degrees at sunset.
The wind Southerly & heavy sea running Went out to pick my troll and found it parted at both Ends and could not get it. Thermometer 61 degrees
Wind South West. Went out early in the morning and swept for my troll untill past noon could not get it Thermometer at 3 P.M. 59 degrees
The wind North West and a heavy breeze Went down and tool up my net torn badly Worked a while in the afternoon turning for R Rand Thermometer 32
Wind Northerly in morning went out fishing and swept for the lost troll got it in the afternoon Winf South west. Thermometer 61 degrees,
Wind South west. fresh breeze Went out a fishing Thermometer at sunset 49 degrees
Wind South Easterly and overcast all day Thermometer 58Â°
Wind South West thick. and blowy. Went out fishing Thermometer 59 degrees

Wind Southerly and thick with fog Wrote letter to J. H. Smallidge Boston. Thermometer. 49 degrees Went. Cherryfield to the Narraguagus Lodge Masonic With Reuben Hammond. late in the aftenoon wind North West rain squalls evening cleared of Came home in night.
Wind North West and fresh breeze Thermometer in morning 33 degrees and at noon 60 degrees work about home on fish

Wind North West. Thermometer at sun rise 31 degrees. and at noon. 54 degrees. In afternoon wrote deed for E. A. Baker and one for H L Norwood In evening started for Ellsworth Went as for West Gouldsboro

Calm in morning left West Gouldsboro at 6 A.M for Ellsworth to see if the Court of Insolvency had discharged me from my debts. the 16th of June Came home in thr afternoon. Wind Southerly and the Thermometer 59 degrees.

Calm in morning left West Gouldsboro at 6 A.M for Ellsworth to see if the Court of Insolvency had discharged me from my debts. the 16th of June Came home in thr afternoon. Wind Southerly and the Thermometer 59 degrees.

Calm in morning left West Gouldsboro at 6 A.M for Ellsworth to see if the Court of Insolvency had discharged me from my debts. the 16th of June Came home in thr afternoon. Wind Southerly and the Thermometer 59 degrees.
Wind North in the morning Went out fishing with Barney Foss. got one tub of large hake to my part wind southerly in afternoon Thermometer 54 degrees received letter from W. F. Vase.
Wind Southerly and overcast with fog and clouds In the evening went to a Prayer meeting at the Hall Thermometer. 62 degrees high
Wind Westerly. and a very fresh breeze with Thermometer 37 degrees at noon Washed out some fish for myself.
Wind Westerly and fresh breeze with the Thermometer 38 degrees worked on my troll in forenoon and in the afternoon. Made window frame for the fishouse that Geo Gerrish fixing to move in
Wind Northerly in morning Thermometer 31Â° heavy frost. Went out fishing Wind Southerly in afternoon Thermometer 50 degrees
Wind South fresh breeze and cloudy Went out fishing. Thermometer at dark when I got home 49 degrees. received letter from Henry Handy
The wind South East Thermometer 54 degrees Wrote letter to Henry Handy at night Commenced raining and blowing very heavy and at 10 PM. rain fell in torrents with a gale of wind.
Wind South South West Thermometer 50 degrees and a very heavy rain in the forenoon cleared up in the afternoon. very heavy sea on the shore
Wind hauled from S.W.to N.West with rain squalls. Thermometer. 44Â° at noon.
Wind North West heavy blow. Thermometer 41Â° hauled to bank the house In afternoon Went to the Marsh acknowledged Administrator deed for Daniel Deasy.
Wind North in morning Thermometer 47 degrees In afternoon wind S. East finished digging my potatoes Geo Gerrish moved in the fish house
The wind Southerly in morning and rainy. and hauled around North West and cleared of. Thermometer at noon 39 degrees. Work in the afternoon on N. A. Bickford Clapboarding front end of his house.
The wind North West Thermometer 33 Registered letter for R.H. Bickford to Geo M Warren. $25 Enclosed
The wind North North West Thermometer in morning 31Â° Started out fishing went as far as Spectacle Island got no bait and came home.
The wind South East. very fresh breeze and a tremendious rain Thermometer 45 degrees Cleared of at night with a gale of wind North.
The wind Westerly. Thermometer 59 degrees work about home.
The wind North West Thermometer 65 degrees. Hauled up 10 loads of Rockweed and went to Presidential Election. GarfieldCandidate. Republican and Hancock Democratic Candidate

Wind Northerly in morning Southerly in afternoon Thermometer 52 degrees at noon Wrote two deed for Sewall Hancock put a cask of oil on board the Schr A. G. Brooks. Subscribed for the N.Y.Sun weekly for three months.
The wind Southerly and very moderate all day Thermometer 61 at noon. Went to So. Gouldsboro and worked all day for Charles L Bunker on shed back at night. received letter from Geo M. Warren
The wind Southerly Thermometer 52 foggy. Grading in front of house.
The wind Southerly and foggy Thermometer 48Â° Went to Religious meeting in Evening
The wind moderate Northerly Thermometer 22 above. Went to Cherryfield to the Masonic Lodge accompanied by Capt AGerrish & N.A.Bickford at 9 PM snowing stoped all night. Cherryfield Hos
The wind North West Thermometer 22 above Went in the woods and got one load of wood. received Card from the Bangor Commercial.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 55Â° Took up my troll to do other work with the intention of heeping it uo untill after I do some farming. Turned Acorn and ball to go on Spire of Chapel.
The wind Baffleing or Calm all day and the Thermometer 55 degrees Went to Steuben to see abt getting lumber and to Millbridge to see R. Fickett & sons Came back at night
The wind Southerly and in the forenoon rainy Thermometer 44 afternoon Cleared up received letter from Stephen Southard Helped Char Pendleton work on dora.
The wind moderate Northerly Thermometer 22 above. Went to Cherryfield to the Masonic Lodge accompanied by Capt AGerrish & N.A.Bickford at 9 PM snowing stoped all night. Cherryfield Hos
The wind North West Thermometer 72 degrees Help J.F. Kingsley haul in 4 loads of hay. had party from Bar Harbor to stay over night
The wind Baffleing or Calm all day and the Thermometer 55 degrees Went to Steuben to see abt getting lumber and to Millbridge to see R. Fickett & sons Came back at night

The wind Southerly and foggy all day Thermometer 50 degrees. took six Hhds salts out of the Black Warrior to use fishing Worked 1/2 day for Barney Foss on his boat to make her tight. received letter from Clarance Hale. Portland.
The wind Westerly and Thermometer 30 degrees above Repairing harness.
The wind W.N.West and snowing a little in the morning Thermometer 24 above zero. Wrote letter to Mrs Bessie E Grant. and kept a copy.

The wind Northerly in the forenoon and Southerly in afternoon Thermometer 48 degrees Work all day for Capt T.H. Smallidge putting in stem for AGBrooks yawl boat. received Check of $16.50 from Wm B Viall for Carrying Mail Route 365
The wind Southerly helped J.F. Kingsley on his hay finished mowing Company left for Bar Harbor Recd letter from Boston Post Went to W Gouldsboro at night and got some ice.
Wind Southerly heavy thunder and lightning early in the morning. Thermometer 52 degrees making out buoys apart of the day.
The wind Westerly Thermometer 56. Work in the house making Curtain Sticks and fixing windows. Had new Shoes put on the Horse. Recd letter from Mrs. J.D. Fernald Boston
The wind Westerly Thermometer 18 above Made sinlk for Capt N A Bickford. received card from Wm B Viall
The wind North East. Thermometer 34 degrees worked 3/4 day for A.M Torry. on Schr Mars Hill at 3.PM commenced to rain stoped work. received letter from Sloan &CO.
The wind Southerly helped J.F. Kingsley on his hay finished mowing Company left for Bar Harbor Recd letter from Boston Post Went to W Gouldsboro at night and got some ice.
Wind Southerly Thermometer 48 Went to So. Gouldsboro Steam boat wharf. and sent Express wagon to Ellsworth via Lamoine for J.W.Davis. Foggy all day.
The wind moderate all day baffling. Thermometer 27 above. light snow in the evening. Work all day on harness getting ready to go in the woods
The wind North West Thermometer 56Â° Went to Ellsworth. with my horse after dishes and Table linnes
The wind South West and very fresh breeze Thermometer 28Â° Wrote letter to Helen B Stevens at Laurence.
The wind Northerly thermometer down to zero. Hauled two loads of wood for my self and one for Capt Peleg Tracy
The wind Southerly helped J.F. Kingsley on his hay finished mowing Company left for Bar Harbor Recd letter from Boston Post Went to W Gouldsboro at night and got some ice.

The wind North East and snowing all day Thermometer 32 above Went to West Gouldsboro on wheels with the mail via Prospect. Wrote letter to Auditor of the Treasury for the Post Office Department Real letter from Mijr Linda Smallidge
Wind South South East. thick and rainy all day. Thermometer 47 degrees.
The wind North East in the morning and looked like snow. with the Thermometer 8 above 0 Went to West Gouldsboro with Mail via Prospect for Mr Weare. received draft of 124.75 from the P.D.Department
The wind moderate Southerly and overcast. Thermometer 58 degrees Hauled in load of hay and left it on the rack

The wind North East and snowing all day Thermometer 32 above Went to West Gouldsboro on wheels with the mail via Prospect. Wrote letter to Auditor of the Treasury for the Post Office Department Real letter from Mijr Linda Smallidge
The wind North West and the Thermometer went from 28 above down to zero. Went in the woods all day hauling out firewood from the stream lot to the Town road.
The wind North West Thermometer 56Â° Went to Ellsworth. with my horse after dishes and Table linnes
Wind Southerly & foggy Commenced farming plowed all day with the help of Henry Sargent. Acknowledged deed for A.J.Baker Thermometer 65
The wind North East in the morning and looked like snow. with the Thermometer 8 above 0 Went to West Gouldsboro with Mail via Prospect for Mr Weare. received draft of 124.75 from the P.D.Department
The wind Easterly and overcast Thermometer 65 Work on exclusion in the Steamer Everett accompanied by wife & child to Sullivan + Bar Harbor

The wind North East and snowing all day Thermometer 32 above Went to West Gouldsboro on wheels with the mail via Prospect. Wrote letter to Auditor of the Treasury for the Post Office Department Real letter from Mijr Linda Smallidge
The wind South East Thermometer at zero in morning. Went to South Gouldsboro. and paid Charles L Bunker for Carrying the mail on Route 365. up to Jan 1 1880.
The wind Easterly. and clear Thermometer  54 Came home from Ellsworth in afternoon.
Wind Northerly in morning went out fishing and set troll wind Southerly in the afternoon took up troll and went home. Thermometer 70Â°
The wind Easterly and overcast Thermometer 65 Work on exclusion in the Steamer Everett accompanied by wife & child to Sullivan + Bar Harbor
The wind North East in the morning and looked like snow. with the Thermometer 8 above 0 Went to West Gouldsboro with Mail via Prospect for Mr Weare. received draft of 124.75 from the P.D.Department
The wind Southerly Thermometer wrote letters to G.S. Peters M Gallery &Co & Eldridge & Perry. Recd letter from Mary Smallidge

The wind North East and snowing all day Thermometer 32 above Went to West Gouldsboro on wheels with the mail via Prospect. Wrote letter to Auditor of the Treasury for the Post Office Department Real letter from Mijr Linda Smallidge
The wind Easterly. and clear Thermometer  54 Came home from Ellsworth in afternoon.
The wind North West Thermometer 18 above. Sent 60 cts to the Bangor Commercial one month pay. Wrote Warranty deed from Silal Foss to Ira B Foss.
Wind Southerly and pleasant Thermometer. 65 degrees Work about home farming Mr Asher Palmer Ordainedin the evening.
The wind Easterly and rainy all day The Thermometer 56Â° Work apart of the day Kneeing abt boat Went to West Gouldsboro at night to Carry Mrs Eunice Kingsley
The wind Easterly and rainy Thermometer 52Â° wrote letter to Mysrs Eldridge & Perry. Sold Massiah Southards horse to Mr W.F. Vose.
The wind West North West Thermometer 40 degrees the roads all clear from Snow
The wind North East in the morning and looked like snow. with the Thermometer 8 above 0 Went to West Gouldsboro with Mail via Prospect for Mr Weare. received draft of 124.75 from the P.D.Department
The wind South East. and snowing in the morning Went in the woods and got one load of wood at 10 AM heavy rain and spoiled the sleding Thermometer 37Â°
Wind South West Thermometer 74 degrees hauling out dressing and getting ready to plant potatoes.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 58 degrees Wrote letter to Mary Smallidge. finished the boat that was begun last winter Recd letter from M. Gallant &Co.

The wind South West Pleasant Thermometer 53 Wrote letter to J.D. Femeld and Stephen Southard. Went to Bar Harbor in my boat & back. Recd letters from S.R. Niles advertising agents. Boston & Abraham French & Co. Dealers in Crocking & glass ware.
The wind North West. Thermometer 39 degrees Went to Bar Harbor in the afternoon and sold three sets of Caster. back at night.
The wind North West Thermometer. 32 degrees
The wind Southerly moderate Thermometer 40Â° work in the afternoon for Capt N. A Bickford
The wind Westerly Thermometer 35 above went to West bay to Town meeting was chosen Constable and sworn in received letter from E Stevens
Calm and hot in the forenoon. Went to West Gouldsboro after seed wheat and grass seed. at noon heavy shower with thunder. Wind came of from the Westward sewed wheat in afternoon Thermometer 70Â°
The wind Westerly Thermometer 35 above went to West bay to Town meeting was chosen Constable and sworn in received letter from E Stevens
The wind Moderate South East and apart of the day foggy. Thermometer 56 Went to a religious meeting in the evening Took boat of for the first time that I finished yesterday

The wind South West Pleasant Thermometer 53 Wrote letter to J.D. Femeld and Stephen Southard. Went to Bar Harbor in my boat & back. Recd letters from S.R. Niles advertising agents. Boston & Abraham French & Co. Dealers in Crocking & glass ware.
The wind North West. Thermometer 39 degrees Went to Bar Harbor in the afternoon and sold three sets of Caster. back at night.
The wind North East and rainy forenoon and in the afternoon wind North Thermometer 32 degrees work all day for Capt N. A. Bickford on the inside of his house.

The wind South West Pleasant Thermometer 53 Wrote letter to J.D. Femeld and Stephen Southard. Went to Bar Harbor in my boat & back. Recd letters from S.R. Niles advertising agents. Boston & Abraham French & Co. Dealers in Crocking & glass ware.
The wind South East Thermometer 58 1/2 degrees Wrote letter to Mr Vose Recieved Mrs Lizzie Amisden the first summer boarder for the season
Wind West North West Thermometer 68 degrees Work all day farming. plowing and hauling dressing. Received a Check from the Post Office for $12.38 for Carrying mail. Route 365
The wind South West Thermometer 37 snow melting very fast. work all day hauling wood wrote letter to Auditor of the Treasury for the PO Department. at Washington D.C.
The wind North West. Thermometer 39 degrees Went to Bar Harbor in the afternoon and sold three sets of Caster. back at night.
The wind North East. and the whole sky looked like snow every minute of the day. but no snow fall. Went to a Religious meeting in the evening

The wind North West. Thermometer 50Â° Went up to the Shore for Baptism but candidate failed to come forward. At night went to the Marsh to be ready for a start To go to Steuben after lumber for outside hog
The wind South East Thermometer 58 degrees fogg most all day. Went to Iron Bernd in my new boat

Wind South East Thermometer 60 overcast and afternoon rainy. At 3 oclock PM Went to a baptism at Steam boat wharf Winter Harbor. and the following persons were baptised. Henry Sargent. Daniel Southard. Jalez Myrick R.M. Torrey. Sarah Torrey Mary Rand Martha Bickford Flora Gerrish Joan Sargent Ruth Pendleton Lillian Namond Sally Bunker Maria Gerrish Alicia Riley Rufuss Bunker Sarah Bunker all by Asher Palmer.

Calm in the morning Thermometer 36 in shade snow melting very fast Hauled two loads of wood from Henry Sargents in the forenoon. and in the afternoon work for Wm Guptill on house Wind North west growing cold at night freezing

Wrote letter to Wm B Viall. The wind North West and very pleasant with the Thermometer 42 degrees. Went to West Gouldsboro and got one doz sets of casters. from Sloan &Co. I being their agent. for Hancock County. to see t sell the celebrated six wheel swing machine Castero.
The wind Northerly & The Thermometer 49 Went to Steuben and got a load of boards and back to West Bay. had them planed and came home at night had Calvin Tracys horse with mine
The wind South East. Thermometer 61Â° racing in morning and again at night heavy showers Went to Lizzie May Ulmers Theatre at Winter Harbor.
The wind Northerly Thermometer 30Â° Wrote letter to Geo H. Brown Ellsworth for Geo Gerrish Work all day for N.A.Bickford
The wind Easterly Thermometer at zero work all day for Wm Guptill on house Wind hauled out Southly Thermometer 24Â° and morning. received Postal Card from Wm B Viall.

Wrote letter to Wm B Viall. The wind North West and very pleasant with the Thermometer 42 degrees. Went to West Gouldsboro and got one doz sets of casters. from Sloan &Co. I being their agent. for Hancock County. to see t sell the celebrated six wheel swing machine Castero.
Wind Easterly and heavy rain all day. Thermometer. 52 degrees. Work in afternoon For F. H. Smallidge hewing nails for fence.
The wind Southerly Came home from Milbridge at noon Thermometer 37 degrees

The wind North East Thermometer 12 above 0 Went to West Gouldsboro to Cary Rebecca Tracy to take the stage for Hancock. Work one half day for Wm Guptill. Snowing all day received letter from Warren Smith Lamoine.

Wrote letter to Wm B Viall. The wind North West and very pleasant with the Thermometer 42 degrees. Went to West Gouldsboro and got one doz sets of casters. from Sloan &Co. I being their agent. for Hancock County. to see t sell the celebrated six wheel swing machine Castero.
The wind Northerly & The Thermometer 49 Went to Steuben and got a load of boards and back to West Bay. had them planed and came home at night had Calvin Tracys horse with mine
The wind West North West in forenoon & clear Thermometer 68 Went to Prospect Harbor with horse work about home most the day Wrote letter to Louis Oshurn & Co.
Wind Southerly nd moderate Thermometer 74Â° Went up new road after piece to make stem for Barney Foss.
The wind North West in the morning moderate in the afternoon the wind breezed up to a gale Thermometer 15 above at night and growing cold work all day for Capt N. A. Bickford.

The wind North East Thermometer 12 above 0 Went to West Gouldsboro to Cary Rebecca Tracy to take the stage for Hancock. Work one half day for Wm Guptill. Snowing all day received letter from Warren Smith Lamoine.

The wind South West and overcast. and sprinkle of rain in the forenoon Thermometer 34 degrees at 10 Am. started for Bar Harbor to sell Sewing Machine castero Wrote letter to Mejrss Sloan &Co. Cincinnati O manufacturer Sewing Machine castero wind North in evening.
The wind N.N.West Thermometer 41Â° degrees Wrote letters to Eldridge &  Perry also Rev Mr. Tripp of Surry
Wind South East most of the forenoon rainy. Wrote petition for J. D. Harrington He applying for the Post Office work in the afternoon for Barney Foss on hos boat stopping leaks Thermometer 64
The wind North West. Thermometer 20 above the wind blowing a gale work all day for N.A. Bickford
The wind West North West in forenoon & clear Thermometer 68 Went to Prospect Harbor with horse work about home most the day Wrote letter to Louis Oshurn & Co.

The wind South West and overcast. and sprinkle of rain in the forenoon Thermometer 34 degrees at 10 Am. started for Bar Harbor to sell Sewing Machine castero Wrote letter to Mejrss Sloan &Co. Cincinnati O manufacturer Sewing Machine castero wind North in evening.

The wind North East Thermometer 12 above 0 Went to West Gouldsboro to Cary Rebecca Tracy to take the stage for Hancock. Work one half day for Wm Guptill. Snowing all day received letter from Warren Smith Lamoine.
The wind South Easterly and the Thermometer 55Â° Commenced building platform around the house Filled out an application for pension for F.P. Gerrish
The wind Southerly and overcast a little showery Thermometer 65 Went to Bar Harbor in Kay Waynard after freight and boots.

The wind South West and overcast. and sprinkle of rain in the forenoon Thermometer 34 degrees at 10 Am. started for Bar Harbor to sell Sewing Machine castero Wrote letter to Mejrss Sloan &Co. Cincinnati O manufacturer Sewing Machine castero wind North in evening.
Wind East fresh breeze and clear Thermometer 65 work all day farming covering potatoes and hauling dresing
The wind North Thermometer 18 above zero. Hauled one load of wood for Peleg Tracy work one fourth day for Wm Guptill on house.
The wind South West Thermometer 32 degrees wrote letter to Capt Horace Handy at Portland. Cut wood at the door.

South East wind overcast Thermometer. Wrote letters to American Office Chas Burrill (of Ellsworth) and F.W. Webber (Cambridgeport) Daily Courier (Lowell)  Mrs. Geddy. Commenced laying platform around house
The wind Southerly and overcast a little showery Thermometer 65 Went to Bar Harbor in Kay Waynard after freight and boots.
The wind North fresh breeze Thermometer 35 degrees Went to Bar Harbor to sell Sewing Machine Casters. Went over on board of the A.G.Brooks.
Wind North East in forenoon. Thermometer 56Â° finished planting potatoes beans & corn Wind South West in afternoon.

The wind Baffling and calm all day Went to Milbridge to the Masonic burial of Capt I Sawyer & wife who perished in the rigging at Barnegat. N.J. Came back home at 7 P.M. The sleighing good moderate rain in evening
The wind Westerly and Thermometer 35 degrees Went to a Religious meeting in the evening at the Hall
The wind Westerly Thermometer 67 1/2 degrees Made axletree stock for my wagon
The wind Southerly and Thermometer 52 finished laying platform on west side of the house
The wind North West in forenoon and S.W. in afternoon Thermometer 72Â°
The wind North fresh breeze Thermometer 35 degrees Went to Bar Harbor to sell Sewing Machine Casters. Went over on board of the A.G.Brooks.
The wind North East Thermometer 32 degrees snowing moderate all the forenoon. about 18 inches snow fall. The biggest storm for the winter so far. Work 1/2 day for N A Bickford.

The wind Baffling and calm all day Went to Milbridge to the Masonic burial of Capt I Sawyer & wife who perished in the rigging at Barnegat. N.J. Came back home at 7 P.M. The sleighing good moderate rain in evening
Wind South West. Thermometer 64 degrees Spaded up the gardens
The wind Westerly and Thermometer 35 degrees work in the afternoon hauling wood.
The wind Southerly and overcast Thermometer 32 degrees above zero. Work all day for Wm Guptill on his house Reef letter from Mejrs Saloun&Co Cincinnatti O.
The wind Northerly in the morning Went to Bar Harbor in Kate Waynard to see abt a party comming over Thermometer 71 degrees Left Bar Harbor at 4:30 pm for home arrived at 6:30

The wind very moderate all day. Thermometer 58Â° Work on platform around house Recd letters from E.A. Baker Springfield Republican Cambridge Conicle Boston Courier L.S. Tripp of Surry and from American Office
Wind South West Thermometer 61 degrees
The wind South South East Thermometer 44 degrees foggy. at night rainy hauling wood all day received Check from the Post Office Department
The wind Southerly Thermometer 34 above work in the forenoon for Wm Guptill. and in the afternoon went. to West Gouldsboro to see the Post Master abt Mail carrier on Route 365.
The wind Northerly in the morning Went to Bar Harbor in Kate Waynard to see abt a party comming over Thermometer 71 degrees Left Bar Harbor at 4:30 pm for home arrived at 6:30

The wind North East in morning hauled around South East in afternoon Went to the baptism of three persons. Mrs Julia Bickford Mrs Direxa Guptill and Mrs. Alma Moon by Mr Whitten The Thermometer 61Â° degrees high in the shade North side of the house.
The wind North fresh breeze Thermometer 35 degrees Went to Bar Harbor to sell Sewing Machine Casters. Went over on board of the A.G.Brooks.
Wind Easterly and Thermometer 59 degrees Started out fishing no bait came back and worked on place
The wind Southerly Thermometer 50Â° Work all day hauling wood from the Stream lot across the Health to the town road.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 34 above work in the forenoon for Wm Guptill. and in the afternoon went. to West Gouldsboro to see the Post Master abt Mail carrier on Route 365.
The wind South East. Thermometer 56Â° Work around the House

The wind South West Thermometer 50 degrees cut wood in the forenoon at the door. Wrote letter to Portland Bangor & Machias Steam boat Co. Capt Wm Handy agrees to give my wife his homestead place for his maintenance.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 68 degrees put down carpet in forenoon And in the afternoon went to Bar Harbor after Mr Stevenson belonging to U.S. Survey boat
Wind East Thermometer 56 drizzling rain. Went out fishing Fannie Pendleton burried in afternoon

The wind Southerly. Thermometer 48 degrees work all day for N. A. Bickford The Sleighing about spailed More wagons than sleighs used. Sent Post Office Check of $12 38 to Wm B Viall Vermont Sent the recipt to the P.O.D
The wind Southerly Thermometer 34 above work in the forenoon for Wm Guptill. and in the afternoon went. to West Gouldsboro to see the Post Master abt Mail carrier on Route 365.
The wind Southerly Thermometer 68 degrees put down carpet in forenoon And in the afternoon went to Bar Harbor after Mr Stevenson belonging to U.S. Survey boat
Wind Southerly and Thermometer 77 at noon Went ou and set my troll in the morning and back at noon Went to Prospect Harbor at night.
Wind South South East Thermometer 43 degrees heavy rain most all day at night the wind South West and clear.
The wind S.S. East Thermometer 49Â°  Wrote letters to S.C. Forsaith E.A. Baker Mrs. J.D. Fernald

The wind South West Thermometer 50 degrees. Went to Ellsworth to get the writings done for Wm Handy where he agrees to convey apart of his real estate to my wife for his maintenance. Got in Ellsworth at noon. The Deed executed by Mr Wiswell came back to Sullivan
The wind North West Thermometer 20 above and pleasant Work all day for Wm Guptill on house received letter from the auditor of the Treasurer for the Post Office Department.
The wind very moderate Southerly and Easterly and thick with fog. Thermometer 79 degrees Went to Prospect with horse to Cary Mr & Mrs Amsdan & Mr Stevenson. Recd Telegraph dispatch from Wm Pendleton.
Wind Southerly Thermometer 78 degrees Work all day for Reuben Rand at his shop ceiling up boat.
The wind West North West. Thermometer 30 degrees worked on half day for N A Bickford and finished work for the present all the lumber used up.
Calm and overcast in forenoon Started for Bar Harbor with Capt R. Pendleton Thermometer 45 at 11 am Took the wind North West and heavy rain came back in afternoon

The wind South West Thermometer 50 degrees. Went to Ellsworth to get the writings done for Wm Handy where he agrees to convey apart of his real estate to my wife for his maintenance. Got in Ellsworth at noon. The Deed executed by Mr Wiswell came back to Sullivan

The wind Southerly Thermometer 32Â° above Went in the woods in the forenoon and out a spar for the A G Brook fhing jilboans in the afternoon work for Wm Guptill Wrote letters to Wm B Viall & Mejses Sloan &Co.
Wind Southerly, and Thermometer 62 degrees Sowed garden in forenoon and in the afternoon went out and took up my troll. Wrote Deed for R H Bickford
Calm and foggy all day Thermometer 74 degrees Made over a pair of oars for myself Recd letter from Mefsr Louis Oshurn & Co. Put down carpet.
The wind West North West Thermometer 80 degrees in shade Work all day for P. A. Summer. repairing Dora at R Rands shop

The wind North West Thermometer from 16 above up to 33 and down to 14 above at night. Wrote a bill of sale of the Schr Nauseag from Celestia A Bickford to n. A Fitzjerald afternoon cutting Ice fo J. F. K.
Calm and overcast in forenoon Started for Bar Harbor with Capt R. Pendleton Thermometer 45 at 11 am Took the wind North West and heavy rain came back in afternoon
The wind South South West Thermometer 55 degrees Came home in the afternoon. received letter from the Auditor of the Post Office Department.

The wind South East. Thermometer 39Â° above worked out half day for Wm Guptill on house. Went to West Gouldsboro to see about P.O.Business. wrote letters to Wm B Viall and Auditor of the P.O.Department received letters from Linda SMallidge & Wm B Viall
Calm and overcast in forenoon Started for Bar Harbor with Capt R. Pendleton Thermometer 45 at 11 am Took the wind North West and heavy rain came back in afternoon
The wind South West Thermometer 34 degrees Work all day hauling Ice for J. F. Kingsley from the Ice pond to the Ice house.

The wind Southerly Thermometer 49 degrees wrote letter to Mr E.A.Baker. Made 2 vite Claim deed for Warren Smith and one for Charles E Smith received letter from Wm B Viall and from Second assistant post Warts Gennd
Wind Westerly. and the Thermometer. 82 degrees at noon. In the afternoon went to West Gouldsboro after Edmond Kingsley
The wind South Easterly And thick with fog. Thermometer 69 degrees work apart of the day fixing up stable. Recd letter from the Capt of the U.S. Steamer Gedna

The wind South East. Thermometer 39Â° above worked out half day for Wm Guptill on house. Went to West Gouldsboro to see about P.O.Business. wrote letters to Wm B Viall and Auditor of the P.O.Department received letters from Linda SMallidge & Wm B Viall
The wind North East fresh breeze and rain Squalls Thermomter 55 Work around the house recieved letters from Alice E Smith Rockland Mary Smallidge and D.W. Joy
The wind North West. Thermometer 42 degrees the ground to soft to haul Ice. Cased out and hung a door for my self in the kitchen.
The wind Southerly. Thermometer 38 foggy wrote letter Julra A. Barnard and Wm B Viall acknowledged for Curtis Stevens.
The wind Southerly and in the fore noon rainy afternoon foggy Thermometer 69 degrees Went to Bar Harbor in my boat to Cary the mail for the US Steamer Gedna

The wind South East. Thermometer 39Â° above worked out half day for Wm Guptill on house. Went to West Gouldsboro to see about P.O.Business. wrote letters to Wm B Viall and Auditor of the P.O.Department received letters from Linda SMallidge & Wm B Viall
The wind North East, in morning fresh breeze at 10 am wind moderate Thermometer 54Â° Went to Bar Harbor With R Pendleton after Mary Smallidge wrote letters to Mrs J.D. Fernald
Wind North all day Thermometer 71 degrees Went to the Lower harbor Claming bought a Dora of S.C Pendleton $2,50
The wind Easterly & Southerly heavy rain all day. work in the forenoon on Ice. finished cutting the Ice and took it out of the water and stacked it up ready to haul Thermometer 40.
The wind South East Thermometer 37 degrees heavy rain storm all day wrote letter to A. Wisell Esq. and Gilbert L. Dennison worked most all day putting ceiling in Mr E A Bakers row boat.
The wind North East, in morning fresh breeze at 10 am wind moderate Thermometer 54Â° Went to Bar Harbor With R Pendleton after Mary Smallidge wrote letters to Mrs J.D. Fernald
Wind North West in the forenoon and South West in the afternoon and Thermometer 74 degrees Washed my wagon and worked apart of the day repairing dora for my self.
The wind North East Thermometer 34 degrees Work for J.F.Kingsley. on Ice and finished cutting Ice house full.

The mail went on wheels The wind Westerly 36 above Work half day for Wm Guptill. Went to District meeting was Chosen moderator. and then Partitioned to the Agent to Call another meeting to Choose a Collector to Collect the district tax.
The wind South Easterly Thermometer 62 degrees rainy most all day heavy with thunder and very sharp lightning
The wind Southerly and apart of the day foggy. Work most all day cutting wood at the door Thermometer 48 degrees at noon

The wind South Easterly Thermometer 49Â° Went to Ellsworth with my horse accompanied by my wife after dishes. Got a load of dishes and came back to West Gouldsboro. and stoped to Mrs. E Kingsley

The wind North West Thermometer 72 degrees work all day on boom for A.G. Brooks Mrs Garvin came to board

The wind Northerly Thermometer 70 degrees work abt home.
